<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897410>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 73–82. Hypatropis inermis (Stål, 1872). 73–74: Habitus dorsal and ventral. 75: Head and thorax lateral; 76: Thoracic external scent efferent system; 77–79: Phallus in dorsal, lateral and ventral view; 80: Genital plates in posteroventral view; 81–82: Female receptaculum seminis and aussenwand. Abbreviations: bc, bucculae; ddr, distal ductus receptaculi; st, secondary thickenings of valvulae 9; ev: evaporatorium; va, vesicular area. Scale bars = 73–74: 1.0 mm; 75, 80–82: 0.5 mm; 76: 500 µm; 77–79: 0.25 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4897410/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897400>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 52–54. Female receptaculum seminis and aussenwand. 52, Hypatropis inermis; 53, Amauromelpia ussu; 54, Stysiana meridionalis. Abbreviations: aaf, anterior annular flange; cs, capsula seminalis; ddr, distal ductus receptaculi; paf, posterior annular flange; pdr, proximal ductus receptaculi; pi, pars intermedialis; la9, laterotergites 9; rs, ring sclerite; tvi, thickening of vaginal intima; va, vesicular area; va9, valvulae 9; vf9, valvifers 9; X, abdominal segment X. Scale bars = 52, 54: 0.5 mm; 53, 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4897400/files/figure.png" .

